  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nHandling various errors over the RPC channel need to be employed.\r\n\r\nSpecifically\r\n\r\n- Requesting too many blocks may result in the peer returning an error and a smaller request should be re-issued (this depends on some standardised error message)\r\n- Handling error cases gracefully with the RPC error response. \r\n- Propagate errors to sync to cancel requests and remove peers from memory\r\n",
